channel.title: Youtube Question
channel.description: I've uploaded a video via Camtasia, but it's not showing up under my channels uploads.. I'm guessing it's because I haven't uploaded it under the channel, but as my user. Can I make the upload appear in my channel's videos?

item.title: Youtube Question

item.description:

No it’s public. It showed up on my news feed or whatever its called in YT, but not under the channel videos, since I didn’t upload it directly to the channel.

item.title: Youtube Question
item.dc:creator: @vManlyMan vManlyMan
item.description:
@vManlyMan wrote:

[quote=“tyb97, post:3, topic:465913”][quote author=vManlyMan link=topic=573034.msg4139360#msg4139360 date=1351993130]
I don’t understand what you mean. If you haven’t uploaded a video to that channel you won’t be able to see it under that channel…
[/quote]
I’ve uploaded a video to my profile, (through Camtasia, so it’s all done automatically), and it uploaded under my profile, but not under my channel. Can I move it so it will show up under my channel’s “video’s” section? Or should I just make a playlist?[/quote]

Is the video set to private or anything? Maybe that’s why you can’t see it in your channel. (I’m not sure exactly how to fix it. I haven’t uploaded any videos to Youtube in a really long time).
